alternative approaches to theatre researchObjectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of the the main theories concerning the visual structure of a theatre performance and its perception. More specifically it covers the theoretical basis of scenography and it components, their creation and critical reception. The course promotes independent thinking, skills on anaysis and synthesis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon succesful completion th student is able to analyze the visual components of a performance, recognize their aims and outcomes study his/her creative work or work by other authors from well-grounded theoretical viewpoints compare different approaches to scenography (creation and analysis) choose and employ suitable frame of reference for his/her subjecy of study distinguish and recognize the theoretical standpoints in various texts synthesize the theory of visual technology into one's own creative work
